public class WaySectioningGraphLoader extends BaseGraphLoader
A GraphLoader that loads edges from a raw graph where each edge is an OSM way, sectioning each edge/way into smaller edges at intersections and according to other rules, as implemented by EdgeSectioner.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)

    • validation

      public com.telenav.kivakit.validation.ValidationType validation()
      Description copied from interface: GraphLoader
      Returns the kind of validation that should be performed on the data loaded by this graph loader. Many graph loaders validate all data with ValidationType.validateAll() but some don't load complete data. An example of an incomplete graph loader is RawPbfGraphLoader, which does not load vertexes or relations. Another is WaySectioningGraphLoader, is incomplete because it does not load relations. These graph loaders may specify another kind of validation.
